fields.name: Museum of Childhood, Good Time Gallery

Type: spelling, strategy
Subject: alphabet, scrabble

fields.history_note: Box lid is printed in colours to show the title and details of the maker together with `Some components imported. 8-Adult, 604-4221 02' and a photograph of the actor Vincent Price against a western town.  Instructions are printed on the inside of the lid
fields.production_note: Milton Bradley ltd, under Berne & universal copyright convention
fields.historical_context_note:
No. of Players: 2
Equipment required: playing trays
letter tiles
instructions

Rules: In the lid of each playing tray is a large dial moulded to show 12 squares, the first is blank and the rest each begin to form the `hangman' symbol and a score from 12 to 0.  Onthe outside of the lid, which faces the opponent, is a window.  As the dial turns to show one of the squares, its picture is shown in the window.  Below the window is a printed panel giving the scores related to each picture.
